but very much from within?

00:26:57.970 --> 00:27:01.360 align:middle line:10%
What if we discovered ways,
secrets, to activate the most

00:27:01.360 --> 00:27:03.727 align:middle line:10%
happiness that you could
have on any given day?

00:27:03.727 --> 00:27:06.310 align:middle line:10%
Well, there's a groundbreaking
study that says it can be done.

00:27:06.310 --> 00:27:07.980 align:middle line:10%
It's called the
Happiness Project,

00:27:07.980 --> 00:27:11.360 align:middle line:10%
a scientifically tested program
that promises, in its essence,

00:27:11.360 --> 00:27:13.791 align:middle line:10%
to rewire your
brain for happiness.

00:27:13.791 --> 00:27:15.290 align:middle line:10%
And joining us now
is the mastermind

00:27:15.290 --> 00:27:17.930 align:middle line:10%
behind the Happiness
Project, Dr. Robert Holden,

00:27:17.930 --> 00:27:19.450 align:middle line:10%
author of the book "Be Happy."

00:27:19.450 --> 00:27:20.284 align:middle line:10%
Happy to see you.

00:27:20.284 --> 00:27:21.200 align:middle line:10%
--Good morning, Diane.

00:27:21.200 --> 00:27:21.860 align:middle line:10%
--Good to have you with us.

00:27:21.860 --> 00:27:22.943 align:middle line:10%
--Thank you for having me.

00:27:22.943 --> 00:27:25.980 align:middle line:10%
--Now, we have been told there
are actual brain scans that

00:27:25.980 --> 00:27:29.700 align:middle line:10%
show, over eight weeks in
this Happiness Project,

00:27:29.700 --> 00:27:30.770 align:middle line:10%
the brain changed.

00:27:30.770 --> 00:27:34.225 align:middle line:10%
The reflexive nature of the
brain changed for happiness?

00:27:34.225 --> 00:27:35.100 align:middle line:10%
--Isn't that amazing?

00:27:35.100 --> 00:27:35.440 align:middle line:10%
Yes.

00:27:35.440 --> 00:27:38.000 align:middle line:10%
It's an eight-week program that
we've been running in the UK

00:27:38.000 --> 00:27:39.344 align:middle line:10%
for 15 years now.

00:27:39.344 --> 00:27:41.010 align:middle line:10%
And basically put,
we've found that when

00:27:41.010 --> 00:27:42.660 align:middle line:10%
people take the
program, they really

00:27:42.660 --> 00:27:45.150 align:middle line:10%
do make positive
changes in their life,

00:27:45.150 --> 00:27:46.770 align:middle line:10%
their work, their relationships.

00:27:46.770 --> 00:27:49.200 align:middle line:10%
But also, it does change
their brain chemistry.

00:27:49.200 --> 00:27:53.730 align:middle line:10%
--And you have said, your anthem
is, you cannot chase happiness,

00:27:53.730 --> 00:27:56.160 align:middle line:10%
but you can choose happiness.

00:27:56.160 --> 00:27:56.894 align:middle line:10%
--Absolutely.

00:27:56.894 --> 00:27:58.310 align:middle line:10%
--And how does
this work, since we

00:27:58.310 --> 00:28:01.440 align:middle line:10%
all wake up to
disappointments in our days?

00:28:01.440 --> 00:28:03.290 align:middle line:10%
You can't get in the skirt.

00:28:03.290 --> 00:28:06.655 align:middle line:10%
You're miserable about what
you have to do that day.

00:28:06.655 --> 00:28:08.749 align:middle line:10%
You're someone facing
the economic crisis

00:28:08.749 --> 00:28:10.040 align:middle line:10%
in the worst way, unemployment.

00:28:10.040 --> 00:28:13.034 align:middle line:10%
How do you choose happiness
on a day like that?

00:28:13.034 --> 00:28:14.450 align:middle line:10%
--Well, I think
the first thing is

00:28:14.450 --> 00:28:17.180 align:middle line:10%
is that the pursuit of happiness
has definitely speeded up.

00:28:17.180 --> 00:28:19.400 align:middle line:10%
We are chasing happiness
faster than we've ever

00:28:19.400 --> 00:28:20.560 align:middle line:10%
chased it before.

00:28:20.560 --> 00:28:24.260 align:middle line:10%
We work faster, we live faster,
we eat faster, we talk faster,

00:28:24.260 --> 00:28:26.320 align:middle line:10%
we breathe faster, we
do everything faster.

00:28:26.320 --> 00:28:28.910 align:middle line:10%
And yet, in this race
towards happiness,

00:28:28.910 --> 00:28:30.990 align:middle line:10%
we somehow haven't
closed the gap.

00:28:30.990 --> 00:28:34.630 align:middle line:10%
So I think we do need to stop
and really rethink happiness

00:28:34.630 --> 00:28:37.100 align:middle line:10%
and ask ourselves,
truly, what is happiness?

00:28:37.100 --> 00:28:39.720 align:middle line:10%
And I think that's so important,
because your definition

00:28:39.720 --> 00:28:42.260 align:middle line:10%
of happiness
ultimately influences

00:28:42.260 --> 00:28:43.640 align:middle line:10%
the rest of your life.

00:28:43.640 --> 00:28:46.044 align:middle line:10%
So start by getting clear
on what happiness is.

00:28:46.044 --> 00:28:46.710 align:middle line:10%
--Getting clear.

00:28:46.710 --> 00:28:49.190 align:middle line:10%
And I am going to run
through the five areas

00:28:49.190 --> 00:28:50.092 align:middle line:10%
very quickly here.

00:28:50.092 --> 00:28:52.050 align:middle line:10%
And then we'll talk in
detail about some of it.

00:28:52.050 --> 00:28:56.190 align:middle line:10%
But attitude-- make up your
mind that you want to be happy.

00:28:56.190 --> 00:28:59.990 align:middle line:10%
Relationships-- you focus, and
focus your essential energy

00:28:59.990 --> 00:29:01.320 align:middle line:10%
on your loved ones.

00:29:01.320 --> 00:29:05.800 align:middle line:10%
Work-- have a passion, not
a job; a purpose, not work.

00:29:05.800 --> 00:29:07.300 align:middle line:10%
Faith-- believe in
something bigger.

00:29:07.300 --> 00:29:09.660 align:middle line:10%
And participate--
don't wait, just do it.

00:29:09.660 --> 00:29:12.410 align:middle line:10%
But I want to bring up a
couple of our audience members

00:29:12.410 --> 00:29:15.620 align:middle line:10%
if I can-- Penelope,
Bobby, and Felicia,

00:29:15.620 --> 00:29:17.370 align:middle line:10%
because we gave some
happiness tests.

00:29:17.370 --> 00:29:17.870 align:middle line:10%
--Yeah.

00:29:17.870 --> 00:29:20.811 align:middle line:10%
We made sure America just tested
themselves on happiness today.

00:29:20.811 --> 00:29:21.310 align:middle line:10%
--Right.

00:29:21.310 --> 00:29:23.060 align:middle line:10%
And Penelope-- raise
your hand over there,

00:29:23.060 --> 00:29:26.840 align:middle line:10%
Penelope-- you got the
hurry-up problem, I gather.

00:29:26.840 --> 00:29:31.230 align:middle line:10%
Tell me what you would say to
Penelope about getting happy

00:29:31.230 --> 00:29:33.570 align:middle line:10%
when she rushes, rushes,
rushes through life.

00:29:33.570 --> 00:29:34.570 align:middle line:10%
How does she begin?

00:29:34.570 --> 00:29:36.514 align:middle line:10%
--Well, Penelope, we
had a conversation.

00:29:36.514 --> 00:29:38.180 align:middle line:10%
And we worked out
that, sometimes, we're

00:29:38.180 --> 00:29:41.790 align:middle line:10%
in such a rush, it's almost like
we have no time to be happy.

00:29:41.790 --> 00:29:42.820 align:middle line:10%
How strange is that?

00:29:42.820 --> 00:29:46.000 align:middle line:10%
It's like we suffer from what
I call destination addiction.

00:29:46.000 --> 00:29:48.020 align:middle line:10%
We hope to be happy one day.

00:29:48.020 --> 00:29:49.990 align:middle line:10%
But really, the art
to happiness is also

00:29:49.990 --> 00:29:51.670 align:middle line:10%
to make time to be happy now.

00:29:51.670 --> 00:29:55.200 align:middle line:10%
So the key today is to
stop once in a while.

00:29:55.200 --> 00:29:58.924 align:middle line:10%
Pay attention to the moments in
your day when you're happiest.

00:29:58.924 --> 00:30:00.340 align:middle line:10%
And see if you can
learn something

00:30:00.340 --> 00:30:03.750 align:middle line:10%
about yourself and your life
by tuning into those moments.

00:30:03.750 --> 00:30:04.860 align:middle line:10%
--So start.

00:30:04.860 --> 00:30:06.620 align:middle line:10%
It's a simple little
habit to develop

00:30:06.620 --> 00:30:08.230 align:middle line:10%
by savoring, stopping to savor.

00:30:08.230 --> 00:30:10.650 align:middle line:10%
--Yeah, and definitely
stop every now and then.

00:30:10.650 --> 00:30:16.120 align:middle line:10%
--Bobby-- overwhelmed, just
over-scheduled, overwhelmed.

00:30:16.120 --> 00:30:17.440 align:middle line:10%
What's the answer?

00:30:17.440 --> 00:30:19.810 align:middle line:10%
--Well, I think, from a
conversation with Bobby,

00:30:19.810 --> 00:30:21.430 align:middle line:10%
what we worked out
is you really have

00:30:21.430 --> 00:30:23.960 align:middle line:10%
to work out why
you wake up today.

00:30:23.960 --> 00:30:26.520 align:middle line:10%
And I think that's a
really good question--

00:30:26.520 --> 00:30:28.230 align:middle line:10%
why have I woken up today?

00:30:28.230 --> 00:30:30.949 align:middle line:10%
What purpose shall I give today?

00:30:30.949 --> 00:30:33.240 align:middle line:10%
And in working out what
purpose you want to give a day,

00:30:33.240 --> 00:30:35.850 align:middle line:10%
I think life becomes a creative
act, because now you're

00:30:35.850 --> 00:30:37.960 align:middle line:10%
not just waiting to
be happy, but you're

00:30:37.960 --> 00:30:39.440 align:middle line:10%
participating in your life.

00:30:39.440 --> 00:30:42.060 align:middle line:10%
You're saying, I can
create my day, too.

00:30:42.060 --> 00:30:44.500 align:middle line:10%
Even though the stock
market goes up and down,

00:30:44.500 --> 00:30:46.807 align:middle line:10%
I can have a say in how my
life is going to be today.

00:30:46.807 --> 00:30:48.390 align:middle line:10%
--Do you believe you
can do it, Bobby?

00:30:48.390 --> 00:30:49.640 align:middle line:10%
--Oh, absolutely.

00:30:49.640 --> 00:30:50.140 align:middle line:10%
Absolutely.

00:30:50.140 --> 00:30:50.670 align:middle line:10%
--All right.

00:30:50.670 --> 00:30:51.430 align:middle line:10%
New way to think.

00:30:51.430 --> 00:30:55.950 align:middle line:10%
And of all the tests we gave,
Felicia is the happiest.

00:30:55.950 --> 00:30:58.720 align:middle line:10%
Welcome to our happiness
champion over there.

00:30:58.720 --> 00:30:59.890 align:middle line:10%
And why is that?

00:30:59.890 --> 00:31:02.020 align:middle line:10%
--Well, firstly, if you
take a look at Felicia,

00:31:02.020 --> 00:31:04.770 align:middle line:10%
I think you are just
joy, if I may say so.

00:31:04.770 --> 00:31:06.660 align:middle line:10%
You've got this smile,
and it's gorgeous.

00:31:06.660 --> 00:31:09.330 align:middle line:10%
But you have said two things
to me that are so important.

00:31:09.330 --> 00:31:11.760 align:middle line:10%
The first is that you
have a strong faith.

00:31:11.760 --> 00:31:14.130 align:middle line:10%
And that is absolutely
a stand out clause.

00:31:14.130 --> 00:31:17.240 align:middle line:10%
If you believe in a god
of unconditional love,

00:31:17.240 --> 00:31:19.549 align:middle line:10%
that supports you in
your life, no end.

00:31:19.549 --> 00:31:21.090 align:middle line:10%
But the other thing
that Felicia has,

00:31:21.090 --> 00:31:23.420 align:middle line:10%
she pays attention
to her relationships.

00:31:23.420 --> 00:31:27.880 align:middle line:10%
She gives her best energy to her
most important relationships.

00:31:27.880 --> 00:31:29.790 align:middle line:10%
And undoubtedly,
that's important,

00:31:29.790 --> 00:31:32.817 align:middle line:10%
because we've been shopping
for happiness for a long time.

00:31:32.817 --> 00:31:35.400 align:middle line:10%
And I don't think we're going
to find it in the shopping list.

00:31:35.400 --> 00:31:37.450 align:middle line:10%
We'll find it in our
relationships and our faith.

00:31:37.450 --> 00:31:39.450 align:middle line:10%
--Yes, and a couple of
other things you've said-

00:31:39.450 --> 00:31:42.550 align:middle line:10%
take a vow of kindness
starting with yourself.

00:31:42.550 --> 00:31:44.490 align:middle line:10%
And mothers particularly
have to do that.

00:31:44.490 --> 00:31:45.700 align:middle line:10%
Be kind to yourself.

00:31:45.700 --> 00:31:47.380 align:middle line:10%
And remember, happiness
is contagious.

00:31:47.380 --> 00:31:49.440 align:middle line:10%
So all around you,
Felicia, people

00:31:49.440 --> 00:31:51.700 align:middle line:10%
are inexplicably
happy this morning.

00:31:51.700 --> 00:31:53.310 align:middle line:10%
And we thank you so much, Dr.--

00:31:53.310 --> 00:31:54.143 align:middle line:10%
[END VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:31:54.143 --> 00:31:56.260 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: So you said
that happiness literally

00:31:56.260 --> 00:31:58.857 align:middle line:10%
influences every decision
you make in your life.

00:31:58.857 --> 00:32:00.440 align:middle line:84%
>>HOLDEN: Your
definition of happiness

00:32:00.440 --> 00:32:02.870 align:middle line:84%
influences every
decision in your life,

00:32:02.870 --> 00:32:05.800 align:middle line:84%
because, for instance, if you
place happiness outside of you,

00:32:05.800 --> 00:32:06.300 align:middle line:90%
guess what?

00:32:06.300 --> 00:32:09.100 align:middle line:84%
Your whole focus is
on outside of you.

00:32:09.100 --> 00:32:10.920 align:middle line:84%
If you know it's
inside of you, you're

00:32:10.920 --> 00:32:12.794 align:middle line:84%
going to make decisions
in a whole other way.

00:32:12.794 --> 00:32:14.490 align:middle line:84%
If you know it's
you, you're going

00:32:14.490 --> 00:32:16.542 align:middle line:84%
to make decisions in the
whole, whole other way.

00:32:16.542 --> 00:32:19.000 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: How do we know what
our definition of happiness is?

00:32:19.000 --> 00:32:20.785 align:middle line:84%
How do we know
that individually?

00:32:20.785 --> 00:32:23.390 align:middle line:84%
>>HOLDEN: We have to
spend some time on that.

00:32:23.390 --> 00:32:24.240 align:middle line:90%
We really do.

00:32:24.240 --> 00:32:26.100 align:middle line:84%
We have to actually
ask ourselves.

00:32:26.100 --> 00:32:27.510 align:middle line:90%
It becomes an inquiry.

00:32:27.510 --> 00:32:30.130 align:middle line:84%
We have to actually really
get to grips with that

00:32:30.130 --> 00:32:32.740 align:middle line:84%
and actually think about
that for ourselves.

00:32:32.740 --> 00:32:35.670 align:middle line:84%
So that's why, really,
I'm a teacher of inquiry.

00:32:35.670 --> 00:32:38.830 align:middle line:84%
I love inquiry, because
inquiry basically

00:32:38.830 --> 00:32:40.500 align:middle line:90%
respects the individual.

00:32:40.500 --> 00:32:42.130 align:middle line:90%
It respects you and me.

00:32:42.130 --> 00:32:44.810 align:middle line:84%
Inquiry is based on the
idea that, really, we

00:32:44.810 --> 00:32:46.850 align:middle line:84%
have the wisdom
within us already.

00:32:46.850 --> 00:32:48.790 align:middle line:90%
Wisdom is never really new.

00:32:48.790 --> 00:32:50.180 align:middle line:90%
Wisdom is remembered.

00:32:50.180 --> 00:32:52.770 align:middle line:84%
You and I, we know
what true happiness is.

00:32:52.770 --> 00:32:55.470 align:middle line:84%
When we stop being neurotic
and running around and being

00:32:55.470 --> 00:32:58.130 align:middle line:84%
manic and busy, we
come back to our heart.

00:32:58.130 --> 00:33:00.640 align:middle line:84%
And our heart knows
what happiness is.

00:33:00.640 --> 00:33:03.860 align:middle line:84%
And when we remember, then
we set the record straight.

00:33:03.860 --> 00:33:07.380 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I was having a
horrible day the other day.

00:33:07.380 --> 00:33:10.450 align:middle line:84%
