things that went wrong.

00:33:10.450 --> 00:33:13.560 align:middle line:84%
Somebody lost a
huge chunk of money.

00:33:13.560 --> 00:33:15.480 align:middle line:84%
And then something
else happened.

00:33:15.480 --> 00:33:17.599 align:middle line:90%
It was just like a cascade.

00:33:17.599 --> 00:33:19.640 align:middle line:84%
And I said to my husband
halfway through the day,

00:33:19.640 --> 00:33:22.380 align:middle line:84%
I said, I feel like
I am in this loop,

00:33:22.380 --> 00:33:28.031 align:middle line:84%
that I'm in this cycle of
catastrophe-- crisis, crisis,

00:33:28.031 --> 00:33:28.530 align:middle line:90%
crisis.

00:33:28.530 --> 00:33:30.030 align:middle line:84%
And I'm waiting for
the next crisis,

00:33:30.030 --> 00:33:31.800 align:middle line:90%
because I'm defending it.

00:33:31.800 --> 00:33:33.950 align:middle line:84%
And so then I get my
daughter in the car.

00:33:33.950 --> 00:33:36.350 align:middle line:84%
We go to her practice,
and I realize

00:33:36.350 --> 00:33:40.040 align:middle line:84%
that I've completely
missed the practice.

00:33:40.040 --> 00:33:42.120 align:middle line:84%
It was at a totally
different time.

00:33:42.120 --> 00:33:45.350 align:middle line:84%
I look at the text, and it was
in a different place and time

00:33:45.350 --> 00:33:46.542 align:middle line:90%
completely.

00:33:46.542 --> 00:33:48.740 align:middle line:84%
And I sat there
with her and went,

00:33:48.740 --> 00:33:50.740 align:middle line:84%
all right, I need to make
a decision right here.

00:33:50.740 --> 00:33:54.140 align:middle line:84%
I'm either going to let her
feel the entire impact of my day

00:33:54.140 --> 00:33:56.930 align:middle line:84%
and everything wrong that has
happened up to this point.

00:33:56.930 --> 00:34:01.280 align:middle line:84%
Or what I chose to do instead
is I rolled my windows down.

00:34:01.280 --> 00:34:03.000 align:middle line:90%
It was a beautiful, breezy day.

00:34:03.000 --> 00:34:05.210 align:middle line:84%
We laid the seat
backs of the car.

00:34:05.210 --> 00:34:06.590 align:middle line:90%
We opened the sun roof.

00:34:06.590 --> 00:34:08.179 align:middle line:90%
And we watched this oak tree.

00:34:08.179 --> 00:34:11.120 align:middle line:84%
And it is burned as an
image in my mind right now

00:34:11.120 --> 00:34:13.000 align:middle line:90%
of just blowing in the wind.

00:34:13.000 --> 00:34:14.500 align:middle line:90%
We turned the music up.

00:34:14.500 --> 00:34:16.500 align:middle line:90%
That song "Happiness" was on.

00:34:16.500 --> 00:34:19.610 align:middle line:84%
And we just cranked it
up and sat there and just

00:34:19.610 --> 00:34:20.319 align:middle line:90%
had a great time.

00:34:20.319 --> 00:34:21.151 align:middle line:90%
>>HOLDEN: Beautiful.

00:34:21.151 --> 00:34:22.560 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And then we fell asleep.

00:34:22.560 --> 00:34:23.800 align:middle line:90%
>>HOLDEN: Wow, really?

00:34:23.800 --> 00:34:25.800 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: We took a 20-minute
cat nap in the sun--

00:34:25.800 --> 00:34:26.080 align:middle line:90%
>>HOLDEN: How cool.

00:34:26.080 --> 00:34:27.014 align:middle line:90%
I love that.

00:34:27.014 --> 00:34:29.449 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: --during
the hour practice.

00:34:29.449 --> 00:34:31.330 align:middle line:90%
It was such a golden moment.

00:34:31.330 --> 00:34:35.780 align:middle line:84%
And what I chose to do after
that was not talk about my day,

00:34:35.780 --> 00:34:39.139 align:middle line:84%
not recreate it, not
tell the story of it,

00:34:39.139 --> 00:34:40.989 align:middle line:84%
not get back into
the cycle of it,

00:34:40.989 --> 00:34:42.679 align:middle line:90%
because it was only going to--

00:34:42.679 --> 00:34:44.949 align:middle line:84%
So then I thought, how much
do we do that in our life?

00:34:44.949 --> 00:34:47.440 align:middle line:84%
How much do we recreate
the childhood trauma,

00:34:47.440 --> 00:34:50.860 align:middle line:84%
the bad relationship,
the horrible boss?

00:34:50.860 --> 00:34:53.670 align:middle line:84%
How do we recreate that every
single moment when we talk

00:34:53.670 --> 00:34:55.060 align:middle line:90%
about it or think about it?

00:34:55.060 --> 00:34:57.690 align:middle line:84%
That's what we're teaching when
we talk to our kids about that,

00:34:57.690 --> 00:34:59.590 align:middle line:84%
is to how to have a
horrible day, a bad boss,

00:34:59.590 --> 00:35:01.160 align:middle line:90%
and really lose a lot of money.

00:35:01.160 --> 00:35:02.980 align:middle line:90%
It's really kind of what we do.

00:35:02.980 --> 00:35:05.090 align:middle line:84%
So that goes back
to the definition.

00:35:05.090 --> 00:35:05.840 align:middle line:90%
>>HOLDEN: It does.

00:35:05.840 --> 00:35:07.970 align:middle line:84%
Can I just say, what I
love about what you've just

00:35:07.970 --> 00:35:09.386 align:middle line:84%
told me there,
though, as well, is

00:35:09.386 --> 00:35:13.105 align:middle line:84%
that you know enough
about happiness already

00:35:13.105 --> 00:35:15.120 align:middle line:84%
that one of the
gifts of happiness

00:35:15.120 --> 00:35:18.410 align:middle line:84%
is that it gives you
the power to reset

00:35:18.410 --> 00:35:20.955 align:middle line:84%
in the middle of
the unhappiness.

00:35:20.955 --> 00:35:22.830 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It's taken a
lot of practice, though.

00:35:22.830 --> 00:35:24.455 align:middle line:84%
>>HOLDEN: Yeah, but
that's what happens

00:35:24.455 --> 00:35:27.550 align:middle line:84%
is the more and more familiar
we get with real happiness,

00:35:27.550 --> 00:35:31.220 align:middle line:84%
it's like we notice when
we're out of balance.

00:35:31.220 --> 00:35:34.170 align:middle line:84%
And initially, we maybe
can't do very much about it.

00:35:34.170 --> 00:35:36.970 align:middle line:84%
But there's that reset
muscle in us, which actually,

00:35:36.970 --> 00:35:39.050 align:middle line:84%
at some point, says,
hold on a minute.

00:35:39.050 --> 00:35:40.170 align:middle line:90%
Stop.

00:35:40.170 --> 00:35:41.760 align:middle line:90%
Stop telling the story.

00:35:41.760 --> 00:35:43.940 align:middle line:84%
Stop chasing whatever I'm
chasing, whatever it is.

00:35:43.940 --> 00:35:46.070 align:middle line:84%
And it's just a
beautiful example for me

00:35:46.070 --> 00:35:48.750 align:middle line:84%
of what we can do when we
know what true happiness is.

00:35:48.750 --> 00:35:51.970 align:middle line:84%
We get that reset
capacity in us to do it.

00:35:51.970 --> 00:35:54.680 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, I was raised
by a raging alcoholic.

00:35:54.680 --> 00:35:55.670 align:middle line:90%
God bless him.

00:35:55.670 --> 00:35:59.910 align:middle line:84%
Vietnam vet and had
post traumatic stress

00:35:59.910 --> 00:36:02.260 align:middle line:90%
and raging fits.

00:36:02.260 --> 00:36:04.320 align:middle line:84%
Things would go flying
into television sets,

00:36:04.320 --> 00:36:07.340 align:middle line:84%
and wooden spoons would
get cracked on a lot of us.

00:36:07.340 --> 00:36:11.820 align:middle line:84%
It was a very
reactive childhood.

00:36:11.820 --> 00:36:14.030 align:middle line:84%
I would always look
for underneath the bed.

00:36:14.030 --> 00:36:20.740 align:middle line:84%
And I had to un-train that
level of reaction in me.

00:36:20.740 --> 00:36:24.360 align:middle line:84%
And those types of cycles
go through generations.

00:36:24.360 --> 00:36:26.810 align:middle line:84%
Studies show they go through
up to five generations

00:36:26.810 --> 00:36:31.090 align:middle line:84%
deep of abuse, rage,
alcoholism, all of that.

00:36:31.090 --> 00:36:33.110 align:middle line:84%
Knowing what I have
been so blessed

00:36:33.110 --> 00:36:34.830 align:middle line:84%
to be able to interview
people like you,

00:36:34.830 --> 00:36:40.750 align:middle line:84%
read your books, throughout
my wonderful experiences,

00:36:40.750 --> 00:36:42.572 align:middle line:90%
is that you can break cycles.

00:36:42.572 --> 00:36:43.530 align:middle line:90%
>>HOLDEN: That's right.

00:36:43.530 --> 00:36:47.380 align:middle line:84%
That's why I wrote "Happiness
Now." "Happiness Now," that

00:36:47.380 --> 00:36:50.340 align:middle line:90%
was a book I wrote back in '98.

00:36:50.340 --> 00:36:53.540 align:middle line:84%
That was the one Oprah found
and why I went on her show.

00:36:53.540 --> 00:36:55.830 align:middle line:84%
"Happiness Now" was
making that stand

00:36:55.830 --> 00:37:00.040 align:middle line:84%
to say that sometimes
happiness is giving up

00:37:00.040 --> 00:37:01.990 align:middle line:90%
all hopes for a better past.

00:37:01.990 --> 00:37:05.070 align:middle line:84%
It's that moment
when we basically

00:37:05.070 --> 00:37:08.000 align:middle line:84%
are able to look at our
past and, instead of saying

00:37:08.000 --> 00:37:10.970 align:middle line:84%
to ourselves, if only
it had been different,

00:37:10.970 --> 00:37:15.250 align:middle line:84%
I would be different now, it's
actually being able to say,

00:37:15.250 --> 00:37:18.480 align:middle line:84%
do you know what, my
past happened exactly

00:37:18.480 --> 00:37:21.330 align:middle line:84%
as it happened, and
it's time to honor that.

00:37:21.330 --> 00:37:26.620 align:middle line:84%
And if I can honor that, then
maybe I can actually let it go,

00:37:26.620 --> 00:37:29.010 align:middle line:84%
let it be in the
past, a place that I

00:37:29.010 --> 00:37:30.750 align:middle line:90%
can revisit whenever I want.

00:37:30.750 --> 00:37:33.450 align:middle line:84%
But I'm going to live
now in this moment.

00:37:33.450 --> 00:37:36.430 align:middle line:90%
That process is sacred.

00:37:36.430 --> 00:37:38.450 align:middle line:84%
Normally, it's a
process described

00:37:38.450 --> 00:37:41.960 align:middle line:84%
as forgiveness
and of letting go.

00:37:41.960 --> 00:37:43.892 align:middle line:90%
And it's vital to happiness.

00:37:43.892 --> 00:37:45.190 align:middle line:90%
It's absolutely vital.

00:37:45.190 --> 00:37:47.039 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I completely
can see that.

00:37:47.039 --> 00:37:48.830 align:middle line:84%
And parenting has been
one of the best ways

00:37:48.830 --> 00:37:51.570 align:middle line:84%
for me to learn that,
because I didn't

00:37:51.570 --> 00:37:53.370 align:middle line:90%
want to repeat the patterns.

00:37:53.370 --> 00:37:55.590 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to create
something new.

00:37:55.590 --> 00:37:58.590 align:middle line:84%
And it gives me the opportunity
every moment to do that.

00:37:58.590 --> 00:38:00.170 align:middle line:90%
Oprah would've been a great mom.

00:38:00.170 --> 00:38:02.120 align:middle line:84%
And she is the
mother to many, where

00:38:02.120 --> 00:38:05.500 align:middle line:84%
she gets to teach
what she learns.

00:38:05.500 --> 00:38:10.310 align:middle line:84%
And also, I completely
forgive my father.

00:38:10.310 --> 00:38:11.900 align:middle line:90%
I mean, my god.

00:38:11.900 --> 00:38:19.220 align:middle line:84%
What he saw and what he
experienced in that war,

00:38:19.220 --> 00:38:23.840 align:middle line:84%
it's amazing that he's still
such an incredible human being.

00:38:23.840 --> 00:38:25.680 align:middle line:90%
So it does enable that.

00:38:25.680 --> 00:38:27.300 align:middle line:90%
And so this is what you do.

00:38:27.300 --> 00:38:29.940 align:middle line:84%
So you have the
Happiness Project.

00:38:29.940 --> 00:38:32.210 align:middle line:84%
And then there's another
one, which I find incredible,

00:38:32.210 --> 00:38:35.154 align:middle line:90%
about the Success Intelligence.

00:38:35.154 --> 00:38:37.070 align:middle line:84%
We talked a little bit
earlier about that link

00:38:37.070 --> 00:38:39.870 align:middle line:90%
between happiness and success.

00:38:39.870 --> 00:38:41.134 align:middle line:90%
>>HOLDEN: Yes.

00:38:41.134 --> 00:38:43.050 align:middle line:84%
Well, let me tell you
about the personal link.

00:38:43.050 --> 00:38:44.980 align:middle line:84%
I mean, the personal
link, really, for me,

00:38:44.980 --> 00:38:47.920 align:middle line:84%
is that I described
the Happiness Project

00:38:47.920 --> 00:38:51.030 align:middle line:90%
as my open letter to my mum.

00:38:51.030 --> 00:38:54.410 align:middle line:84%
And I think of Success
Intelligence as my open letter

00:38:54.410 --> 00:38:54.970 align:middle line:90%
to my dad.

00:38:54.970 --> 00:38:55.920 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Nice.

00:38:55.920 --> 00:38:57.510 align:middle line:84%
>>HOLDEN: And the
Happiness Project

00:38:57.510 --> 00:39:00.270 align:middle line:84%
is a meditation on
what is real happiness.

00:39:00.270 --> 00:39:02.630 align:middle line:84%
And Success Intelligence
is a meditation

00:39:02.630 --> 00:39:04.190 align:middle line:90%
on what is real success.

00:39:04.190 --> 00:39:05.980 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What is real success?

00:39:05.980 --> 00:39:06.980 align:middle line:90%
What is it?

00:39:06.980 --> 00:39:07.830 align:middle line:90%
I'm asking you.

00:39:07.830 --> 00:39:08.500 align:middle line:90%
>>HOLDEN: OK.

00:39:08.500 --> 00:39:13.573 align:middle line:84%
Well, for me, I would
have to say it's love.

00:39:13.573 --> 00:39:18.970 align:middle line:84%
If your definition of success
has little or no mention

00:39:18.970 --> 00:39:22.710 align:middle line:84%
of love, get another
definition as fast as possible.

00:39:22.710 --> 00:39:24.100 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:39:24.100 --> 00:39:25.851 align:middle line:90%
>>HOLDEN: It has to be love.

00:39:25.851 --> 00:39:29.660 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What is it you hear
mostly, definition of success?

00:39:29.660 --> 00:39:30.675 align:middle line:90%
Having X, Y, Z?

00:39:30.675 --> 00:39:31.300 align:middle line:90%
>>HOLDEN: Yeah.

00:39:31.300 --> 00:39:35.090 align:middle line:84%
It goes along the same
lines as happiness.

00:39:35.090 --> 00:39:36.755 align:middle line:84%
It's all about
having and getting

00:39:36.755 --> 00:39:38.660 align:middle line:90%
and wanting and chasing.

00:39:38.660 --> 00:39:43.280 align:middle line:84%
And everybody goes down
that line for a while,

00:39:43.280 --> 00:39:45.300 align:middle line:84%
to the point where
we satisfy ourselves

00:39:45.300 --> 00:39:47.490 align:middle line:90%
that it isn't real success.

00:39:47.490 --> 00:39:49.450 align:middle line:84%
It's like a phase we
have to go through.

00:39:49.450 --> 00:39:50.045 align:middle line:90%
And we do it.

00:39:50.045 --> 00:39:50.920 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I've done it.

00:39:50.920 --> 00:39:51.320 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, absolutely.

00:39:51.320 --> 00:39:51.990 align:middle line:90%
>>HOLDEN: Yeah, we all do it.

00:39:51.990 --> 00:39:53.760 align:middle line:90%
And I encourage people to do it.

00:39:53.760 --> 00:39:55.320 align:middle line:90%
Get it over and done with.

00:39:55.320 --> 00:39:56.070 align:middle line:90%
That's my feeling.

00:39:56.070 --> 00:39:56.750 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: The acquiring,
having thing.

00:39:56.750 --> 00:39:58.590 align:middle line:84%
>>HOLDEN: Yeah, go
and get your BMW.

00:39:58.590 --> 00:40:00.030 align:middle line:90%
Do what you need to do.

00:40:00.030 --> 00:40:03.019 align:middle line:84%
And enjoy it, as
well, by the way.

00:40:03.019 --> 00:40:04.560 align:middle line:84%
It's not that these
things are wrong.

00:40:04.560 --> 00:40:08.180 align:middle line:84%
It's just that they
don't make you happy.

00:40:08.180 --> 00:40:11.480 align:middle line:84%
One of the keys to
happiness is to understand

00:40:11.480 --> 00:40:14.300 align:middle line:90%
that nothing makes you happy.

00:40:14.300 --> 00:40:18.350 align:middle line:84%
If you can get that,
then you're free.

00:40:18.350 --> 00:40:20.880 align:middle line:84%
Nothing in this
world makes us happy.

00:40:20.880 --> 00:40:23.870 align:middle line:84%
Everything in this world can
encourage us to be happy.

00:40:23.870 --> 00:40:25.910 align:middle line:90%
But nothing can make us happy.

00:40:25.910 --> 00:40:28.460 align:middle line:84%
Once you've got
that, once you know

00:40:28.460 --> 00:40:31.430 align:middle line:84%
that you've arrived with
the happiness already,

00:40:31.430 --> 00:40:33.420 align:middle line:84%
then you're free
to enjoy the world.

00:40:33.420 --> 00:40:37.120 align:middle line:84%
Now you can go shopping for fun
rather than thinking shopping

00:40:37.120 --> 00:40:38.410 align:middle line:90%
is the purpose of your life.

00:40:38.410 --> 00:40:41.000 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Window shopping
is just as satisfying

00:40:41.000 --> 00:40:41.970 align:middle line:90%
when you realize that.

00:40:41.970 --> 00:40:43.740 align:middle line:90%
>>HOLDEN: You can shop for fun.

00:40:43.740 --> 00:40:45.850 align:middle line:84%
But it's just not the
purpose of your life.

00:40:45.850 --> 00:40:47.920 align:middle line:84%
And once you know that,
that's really cool.

00:40:47.920 --> 00:40:50.220 align:middle line:84%
In the same way,
with success, it's

00:40:50.220 --> 00:40:56.120 align:middle line:84%
like you have to go through
some of the counterfeit coins

00:40:56.120 --> 00:40:58.052 align:middle line:90%
to get to the real gold.

00:40:58.052 --> 00:41:00.260 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You just said
something really, really great.

00:41:00.260 --> 00:41:03.730 align:middle line:84%
You said, as long
as we don't realize

00:41:03.730 --> 00:41:05.650 align:middle line:84%
that outside things
make us happy,

00:41:05.650 --> 00:41:10.360 align:middle line:84%
but you've already
arrived with happiness.

00:41:10.360 --> 00:41:11.310 align:middle line:90%
Detail that for me.

00:41:11.310 --> 00:41:13.610 align:middle line:90%
You arrive with happiness.

00:41:13.610 --> 00:41:15.150 align:middle line:90%
Arrive where?

00:41:15.150 --> 00:41:15.650 align:middle line:90%
Here?

00:41:15.650 --> 00:41:16.274 align:middle line:90%
>>HOLDEN: Here.

00:41:16.274 --> 00:41:17.430 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely here.

00:41:17.430 --> 00:41:20.050 align:middle line:90%
Something happens to us, Lisa.

00:41:20.050 --> 00:41:22.390 align:middle line:84%
And it happens in different
ways to all of us.

00:41:22.390 --> 00:41:26.920 align:middle line:84%
But we experience
a fall from grace.

00:41:26.920 --> 00:41:30.880 align:middle line:84%
The fall from grace is
where, for some reason,

00:41:30.880 --> 00:41:35.690 align:middle line:84%
we lose touch with our
true nature, what I call--

00:41:35.690 --> 00:41:37.130 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Happens around our 20s.

00:41:37.130 --> 00:41:37.640 align:middle line:90%
20s, 30s.

00:41:37.640 --> 00:41:39.684 align:middle line:90%
>>HOLDEN: Yeah.

00:41:39.684 --> 00:41:41.100 align:middle line:84%
It's where we lose
touch with what

00:41:41.100 --> 00:41:43.470 align:middle line:90%
I call the unconditioned self.

00:41:43.470 --> 00:41:46.570 align:middle line:84%
Now, the unconditioned self
is just our true nature.

00:41:46.570 --> 00:41:49.910 align:middle line:84%
And really, happiness
is our true nature.

00:41:49.910 --> 00:41:54.310 align:middle line:84%
Happiness is you
minus your neurosis.

00:41:54.310 --> 00:41:55.480 align:middle line:90%
That's all happiness is.

00:41:55.480 --> 00:41:56.896 align:middle line:90%
It's just you.

00:41:56.896 --> 00:42:01.970 align:middle line:90%
Love is you minus your neurosis.

00:42:01.970 --> 00:42:05.170 align:middle line:84%
Everything you need for success,
you arrived with that already.

00:42:05.170 --> 00:42:06.920 align:middle line:90%
It's in your being.

00:42:06.920 --> 00:42:10.260 align:middle line:84%
Now, the thing is, in our
world, we don't do being.

00:42:10.260 --> 00:42:13.787 align:middle line:84%
We do doing, going, wanting,
having, learning, helping,

00:42:13.787 --> 00:42:15.620 align:middle line:84%
chasing-- bum, bum,
bum, bum, bum, bum, bum.

00:42:15.620 --> 00:42:16.080 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Absolutely.

00:42:16.080 --> 00:42:17.640 align:middle line:84%
And that's what
we're marketed to do.

00:42:17.640 --> 00:42:17.960 align:middle line:90%
>>HOLDEN: Yes.

00:42:17.960 --> 00:42:19.960 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: We're marketed
to this prescription will

00:42:19.960 --> 00:42:23.404 align:middle line:84%
make you feel this way
and romantic and all that.

00:42:23.404 --> 00:42:25.570 align:middle line:84%
>>HOLDEN: In the cultures
that you and I grew up in,

00:42:25.570 --> 00:42:26.910 align:middle line:90%
we're not beings.

00:42:26.910 --> 00:42:28.560 align:middle line:90%
We're consumers.

00:42:28.560 --> 00:42:30.500 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Magazines,
articles, billboards--

00:42:30.500 --> 00:42:32.450 align:middle line:90%
you see them all day, every day.

00:42:32.450 --> 00:42:34.715 align:middle line:84%
How many-- 3,000 images--
are given to you a day

00:42:34.715 --> 00:42:35.340 align:middle line:90%
of what to buy?

00:42:35.340 --> 00:42:35.600 align:middle line:90%
>>HOLDEN: Exactly.

00:42:35.600 --> 00:42:35.900 align:middle line:90%
That's right.

00:42:35.900 --> 00:42:36.691 align:middle line:90%
That's the average.

00:42:36.691 --> 00:42:39.535 align:middle line:84%
And if you live in a
city, it's 3,000-plus.

00:42:39.535 --> 00:42:41.160 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Unless you're
in Colorado here,

00:42:41.160 --> 00:42:42.534 align:middle line:84%
where they don't
have billboards.

00:42:42.534 --> 00:42:44.970 align:middle line:84%
But when you have that
idea of everywhere

00:42:44.970 --> 00:42:48.270 align:middle line:84%
you look is being told, you
need to do this to be happy,

00:42:48.270 --> 00:42:49.850 align:middle line:84%
you need to buy
this to be happy,

00:42:49.850 --> 00:42:52.480 align:middle line:84%
you need to go this
place to be happy.

00:42:52.480 --> 00:42:54.480 align:middle line:84%
Every external message
out there tells you

00:42:54.480 --> 00:42:55.730 align:middle line:90%
happiness is outside yourself.

00:42:55.730 --> 00:42:57.080 align:middle line:90%
>>HOLDEN: It's absolutely right.

00:42:57.080 --> 00:43:02.040 align:middle line:84%
I wrote a book called "Shift
Happens." "Shift Happens"

00:43:02.040 --> 00:43:04.340 align:middle line:84%
is a book where I
made a distinction

00:43:04.340 --> 00:43:07.950 align:middle line:84%
between self-improvement
and self-acceptance.

00:43:07.950 --> 00:43:09.540 align:middle line:84%
And in that book,
I made the point

00:43:09.540 --> 00:43:13.570 align:middle line:84%
that, actually, no amount
of self-improvement

00:43:13.570 --> 00:43:17.370 align:middle line:84%
can make up for any
lack of self-acceptance.

00:43:17.370 --> 00:43:20.760 align:middle line:84%
Self-acceptance is
where you accept

00:43:20.760 --> 00:43:23.270 align:middle line:84%
that you are the happiness
you're looking for,

00:43:23.270 --> 00:43:25.810 align:middle line:84%
that you are the love
you're looking for.

00:43:25.810 --> 00:43:28.180 align:middle line:84%
If you won't accept
that, then it

00:43:28.180 --> 00:43:30.394 align:middle line:84%
doesn't matter how much you
try to improve yourself.

00:43:30.394 --> 00:43:32.935 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't matter how beautiful
you try to make yourself look

00:43:32.935 --> 00:43:35.580 align:middle line:84%
or how successful you try
to make yourself look.

00:43:35.580 --> 00:43:39.120 align:middle line:84%
You'll never feel like you've
improved yourself enough.

00:43:39.120 --> 00:43:42.163 align:middle line:84%
This is why self-improvement
is so exhausting for all of us.

00:43:42.163 --> 00:43:42.990 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:43:42.990 --> 00:43:44.010 align:middle line:90%
It's such a pursuit.

00:43:44.010 --> 00:43:45.590 align:middle line:90%
>>HOLDEN: It's such a pursuit.

00:43:45.590 --> 00:43:48.440 align:middle line:84%
What we're telling ourselves
is, I'm not ready for happiness

00:43:48.440 --> 00:43:51.140 align:middle line:84%
yet, I'm not ready for love yet,
I'm not ready for success yet.

00:43:51.140 --> 00:43:52.306 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I'm not good enough.

00:43:52.306 --> 00:43:54.530 align:middle line:84%
>>HOLDEN: I'll be ready
for it soon, apparently,

00:43:54.530 --> 00:43:56.680 align:middle line:90%
in about 18 months' time.

00:43:56.680 --> 00:43:59.190 align:middle line:84%
But that 18 months
never gets any closer.

00:43:59.190 --> 00:44:01.250 align:middle line:84%
And our whole life,
we're chasing,

00:44:01.250 --> 00:44:03.460 align:middle line:84%
and we're trying to
improve ourselves in order

00:44:03.460 --> 00:44:07.274 align:middle line:84%
to be happier, to be
successful, to be more loving.

00:44:07.274 --> 00:44:08.690 align:middle line:84%
I think one of the
greatest things

00:44:08.690 --> 00:44:11.600 align:middle line:84%
we can do for
ourselves is to just

00:44:11.600 --> 00:44:15.780 align:middle line:84%
be willing, just for a moment,
to see what's it like to be me

00:44:15.780 --> 00:44:18.720 align:middle line:84%
when I'm not trying
to improve myself.

00:44:18.720 --> 00:44:21.050 align:middle line:84%
Literally, what's
it like to be me

00:44:21.050 --> 00:44:22.720 align:middle line:84%
when I'm not trying
to improve myself?

00:44:22.720 --> 00:44:26.470 align:middle line:84%
And I tell you, when people
sit with that for five minutes,

00:44:26.470 --> 00:44:28.470 align:middle line:84%
they start to feel really
good about themselves.

00:44:28.470 --> 00:44:29.450 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Absolutely.

00:44:29.450 --> 00:44:31.200 align:middle line:84%
>>HOLDEN: And what
they're connecting with

00:44:31.200 --> 00:44:33.230 align:middle line:84%
is the joy that we're
meant to follow,

00:44:33.230 --> 00:44:36.525 align:middle line:84%
the love that's trying to guide
us and bless us and inspire us

00:44:36.525 --> 00:44:37.070 align:middle line:90%
in our life.

00:44:37.070 --> 00:44:37.780 align:middle line:90%
It's all there.

00:44:37.780 --> 00:44:39.380 align:middle line:90%
It's all there.

00:44:39.380 --> 00:44:41.540 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And I love that
you give us practical ways

00:44:41.540 --> 00:44:43.050 align:middle line:90%
to be able to get to that place.

00:44:43.050 --> 00:44:45.400 align:middle line:90%
I love the idea of "Holy Shift."

00:44:45.400 --> 00:44:47.490 align:middle line:90%
This is-- explain it if you can.

00:44:47.490 --> 00:44:49.820 align:middle line:84%
It's the "Course in
Miracles" brought to you

00:44:49.820 --> 00:44:51.210 align:middle line:90%
in easy, digestible chunks.

00:44:51.210 --> 00:44:52.020 align:middle line:90%
>>HOLDEN: Yay, "Holy Shift."

00:44:52.020 --> 00:44:54.145 align:middle line:84%
Well, I've been a student
of "A Course in Miracles"

00:44:54.145 --> 00:44:55.390 align:middle line:90%
for 20 years.

00:44:55.390 --> 00:44:58.710 align:middle line:84%
And "A Course in Miracles"
is a publishing phenomenon,

00:44:58.710 --> 00:45:01.100 align:middle line:84%
because it has sold
millions of copies,

00:45:01.100 --> 00:45:03.270 align:middle line:90%
but hardly anybody's read it.

00:45:03.270 --> 00:45:05.130 align:middle line:84%
And the reason why
hardly anybody's read it

00:45:05.130 --> 00:45:08.185 align:middle line:84%
is because it's, like,
1,500 pages of full-on text.

00:45:08.185 --> 00:45:09.810 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Yeah, it's
difficult to digest.

00:45:09.810 --> 00:45:10.560 align:middle line:90%
>>HOLDEN: It's so hard.

00:45:10.560 --> 00:45:11.320 align:middle line:90%
It is so hard.

00:45:11.320 --> 00:45:13.380 align:middle line:84%
Most of us, we put it
on our bookshelves,

00:45:13.380 --> 00:45:18.170 align:middle line:84%
and we just let
the glow help us.

00:45:18.170 --> 00:45:20.350 align:middle line:84%
And we want to read
it, and we can't.

00:45:20.350 --> 00:45:21.140 align:middle line:90%
So what do we do?

00:45:21.140 --> 00:45:22.756 align:middle line:90%
We go to Marianne Williamson.

00:45:22.756 --> 00:45:24.380 align:middle line:84%
Thank the lord for
Marianne Williamson.

00:45:24.380 --> 00:45:26.080 align:middle line:90%
We read "A Return to Love."

00:45:26.080 --> 00:45:28.400 align:middle line:84%
And we find other people
have written beautiful books

00:45:28.400 --> 00:45:30.180 align:middle line:90%
about "A Course in Miracles."

00:45:30.180 --> 00:45:32.200 align:middle line:84%
What I wanted to do
with "Holy Shift"

00:45:32.200 --> 00:45:37.200 align:middle line:84%
was to create a day book of
excerpts from the course.

00:45:37.200 --> 00:45:39.520 align:middle line:84%
So this is purely
"Course in Miracles"

00:45:39.520 --> 00:45:41.860 align:middle line:90%
material and excerpted.

00:45:41.860 --> 00:45:45.630 align:middle line:84%
So I've taken 365 of
my favorite sayings,

00:45:45.630 --> 00:45:47.810 align:middle line:84%
and I've put them
into a day book.

00:45:47.810 --> 00:45:49.720 align:middle line:84%
And you can just
open it up and--

00:45:49.720 --> 00:45:50.240 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Just like I am now.

00:45:50.240 --> 00:45:50.670 align:middle line:90%
>>HOLDEN: Yeah.

00:45:50.670 --> 00:45:52.128 align:middle line:84%
And you'll hopefully
find something

00:45:52.128 --> 00:45:55.470 align:middle line:84%
that really resonates
and just make sense.

00:45:55.470 --> 00:45:59.110 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Oh, you say, "You
believe that without the ego,

00:45:59.110 --> 00:46:01.250 align:middle line:90%
all would be chaos.

00:46:01.250 --> 00:46:04.960 align:middle line:84%
Yet, I assure you that without
the ego, all would be love."

00:46:04.960 --> 00:46:07.220 align:middle line:84%
And you take one of
these daily quotes

00:46:07.220 --> 00:46:10.624 align:middle line:84%
and just approach your entire
day with that philosophy.

00:46:10.624 --> 00:46:12.290 align:middle line:84%
>>HOLDEN: That's a
beautiful meditation.

00:46:12.290 --> 00:46:14.990 align:middle line:84%
So can you read that
one to me again?

00:46:14.990 --> 00:46:16.750 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: "You believe
that without the ego,

00:46:16.750 --> 00:46:17.950 align:middle line:90%
all would be chaos.

00:46:17.950 --> 00:46:22.015 align:middle line:84%
Yet, I assure you that without
the ego, all would be love."

00:46:22.015 --> 00:46:24.990 align:middle line:84%
>>HOLDEN: OK, so if we just took
a moment and said, OK, hold on.

00:46:24.990 --> 00:46:28.806 align:middle line:84%
What if, today, instead of
what does the ego love to do,

00:46:28.806 --> 00:46:29.680 align:middle line:90%
let's think about it.

00:46:29.680 --> 00:46:31.250 align:middle line:90%
The ego loves to judge.

00:46:31.250 --> 00:46:32.770 align:middle line:90%
I'm always judging myself.

00:46:32.770 --> 00:46:35.400 align:middle line:84%
All right, just
for five minutes,

00:46:35.400 --> 00:46:37.100 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to see what
it's like to be me

00:46:37.100 --> 00:46:38.845 align:middle line:90%
when I'm not judging myself.

00:46:38.845 --> 00:46:41.760 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to give up
judgment for five minutes.

00:46:41.760 --> 00:46:42.750 align:middle line:90%
It should be OK.

00:46:42.750 --> 00:46:43.810 align:middle line:90%
Everything will be fine.

00:46:43.810 --> 00:46:45.510 align:middle line:90%
It won't be that chaotic.

00:46:45.510 --> 00:46:46.720 align:middle line:90%
And I just sit for a moment.

00:46:46.720 --> 00:46:48.450 align:middle line:90%
And I just go, hold on a minute.

00:46:48.450 --> 00:46:51.036 align:middle line:84%
This is me when I'm
not judging myself.

00:46:51.036 --> 00:46:52.540 align:middle line:90%
This feels good.

00:46:52.540 --> 00:46:55.580 align:middle line:90%
This feels really, really good.

00:46:55.580 --> 00:46:57.700 align:middle line:84%
OK, I've been judging
myself my whole life.

00:46:57.700 --> 00:46:58.730 align:middle line:90%
Where's it got me?

00:46:58.730 --> 00:47:00.230 align:middle line:84%
Let's think about
this for a minute.

00:47:00.230 --> 00:47:04.470 align:middle line:84%
I mean, seriously, how well
have I done by judging myself?

00:47:04.470 --> 00:47:08.040 align:middle line:84%
And it occurs to me that,
well, actually, it's not really

00:47:08.040 --> 00:47:09.520 align:middle line:90%
been that good for me.

00:47:09.520 --> 00:47:12.460 align:middle line:84%
I can't honestly say to you
that the success of my life

00:47:12.460 --> 00:47:16.440 align:middle line:84%
is down to the fact that I've
judged myself consistently,

00:47:16.440 --> 00:47:19.716 align:middle line:90%
24/7, for 30 years.

00:47:19.716 --> 00:47:21.440 align:middle line:84%
That's what these
types of meditations

00:47:21.440 --> 00:47:22.370 align:middle line:90%
are asking us to do.

00:47:22.370 --> 00:47:23.832 align:middle line:90%
They're asking is just to stop.

00:47:23.832 --> 00:47:25.790 align:middle line:84%
That's the first thing
in a spiritual practice.

00:47:25.790 --> 00:47:26.440 align:middle line:90%
Stop.

00:47:26.440 --> 00:47:27.520 align:middle line:90%
Stop telling your story.

00:47:27.520 --> 00:47:28.480 align:middle line:90%
Stop being an ego.

00:47:28.480 --> 00:47:30.100 align:middle line:90%
Stop being your self-image.

00:47:30.100 --> 00:47:32.570 align:middle line:84%
And let's just see what it's
like to be you when you're not

00:47:32.570 --> 00:47:35.900 align:middle line:84%
chasing the happiness, when
you're not searching for love,

00:47:35.900 --> 00:47:39.190 align:middle line:90%
when you're not after success.

00:47:39.190 --> 00:47:41.190 align:middle line:84%
Let's just see what it's
like to be you already,

00:47:41.190 --> 00:47:42.740 align:middle line:90%
before you go shopping.

00:47:42.740 --> 00:47:45.270 align:middle line:84%
Maybe, maybe, what
you're shopping

00:47:45.270 --> 00:47:46.830 align:middle line:90%
for is what you already are.

00:47:46.830 --> 00:47:48.580 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You can
apply that to eating,

00:47:48.580 --> 00:47:50.300 align:middle line:90%
as well, emotional eating.

00:47:50.300 --> 00:47:52.380 align:middle line:84%
You can really stop
judging yourself

00:47:52.380 --> 00:47:54.640 align:middle line:84%
about what you
look like and then

00:47:54.640 --> 00:47:58.130 align:middle line:84%
be mindful in what you're
putting in your mouth

00:47:58.130 --> 00:48:00.370 align:middle line:90%
and in what reason.

00:48:00.370 --> 00:48:02.650 align:middle line:84%
Is this because I'm
trying to create comfort

00:48:02.650 --> 00:48:03.850 align:middle line:90%
in a difficult situation?

00:48:03.850 --> 00:48:06.064 align:middle line:84%
Well, maybe I should
look at the situation.

00:48:06.064 --> 00:48:06.980 align:middle line:90%
Those types of things.

00:48:06.980 --> 00:48:08.160 align:middle line:90%
>>HOLDEN: Totally.

00:48:08.160 --> 00:48:11.086 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you did this really
great piece on leadership.

00:48:11.086 --> 00:48:12.460 align:middle line:84%
And I think that
everything we've

00:48:12.460 --> 00:48:14.610 align:middle line:84%
talked about up to this
point, about happiness

00:48:14.610 --> 00:48:19.490 align:middle line:84%
and about Success Intelligence,
the next evolution of that

00:48:19.490 --> 00:48:22.045 align:middle line:90%
is leadership, I believe.

00:48:22.045 --> 00:48:23.170 align:middle line:90%
>>HOLDEN: I agree with you.

00:48:23.170 --> 00:48:25.100 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: We're going to
take a quick look at this,

00:48:25.100 --> 00:48:26.599 align:middle line:84%
because I think
it's very important.

00:48:26.599 --> 00:48:29.035 align:middle line:84%
Take a look at Robert Holden
talking about leadership.

00:48:29.035 --> 00:48:29.490 align:middle line:90%
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:48:29.490 --> 00:48:30.970 align:middle line:84%
--My starting point
with leadership

00:48:30.970 --> 00:48:33.110 align:middle line:84%
is that leadership
isn't a position.

00:48:33.110 --> 00:48:34.550 align:middle line:90%
It's not a job title.

00:48:34.550 --> 00:48:35.940 align:middle line:90%
It's not a pay grade.

00:48:35.940 --> 00:48:39.670 align:middle line:84%
I think it's more a way of
showing up in the world.

00:48:39.670 --> 00:48:41.820 align:middle line:84%
And leadership
starts with the idea

00:48:41.820 --> 00:48:44.290 align:middle line:84%
that, really, the
world is an effect.

00:48:44.290 --> 00:48:45.725 align:middle line:90%
It's an effect of us.

00:48:45.725 --> 00:48:47.350 align:middle line:84%
So if we want to see
a different world,

00:48:47.350 --> 00:48:50.530 align:middle line:84%
we just have to be willing
to show up differently.

00:48:50.530 --> 00:48:52.530 align:middle line:84%
Now, the four areas
that I've covered,

00:48:52.530 --> 00:48:54.990 align:middle line:84%
the first one was all
about that leadership

00:48:54.990 --> 00:48:57.410 align:middle line:84%
is about being more
of who you really are.

00:48:57.410 --> 00:48:59.545 align:middle line:84%
So it's not just about
putting on a suit

00:48:59.545 --> 00:49:02.360 align:middle line:84%
and showing up in a certain
role and being a certain way.

00:49:02.360 --> 00:49:05.180 align:middle line:84%
It's actually being more
of who you really are.

00:49:05.180 --> 00:49:08.610 align:middle line:84%
If you think something
is missing at work,

00:49:08.610 --> 00:49:10.830 align:middle line:84%
if you think something
is missing in a project,

00:49:10.830 --> 00:49:13.140 align:middle line:84%
if you think something is
missing in a conversation,

00:49:13.140 --> 00:49:17.290 align:middle line:84%
maybe what's missing is
you, more of the real you.

00:49:17.290 --> 00:49:19.380 align:middle line:90%
So that's my starting point.

00:49:19.380 --> 00:49:21.470 align:middle line:84%
After that, I'm
suggesting that leadership

00:49:21.470 --> 00:49:26.310 align:middle line:84%
is all about making sure the
team understands what's real,

00:49:26.310 --> 00:49:28.550 align:middle line:84%
that we know what our
real strengths are,

00:49:28.550 --> 00:49:31.210 align:middle line:84%
our real purpose are, and
what our real vision is.

00:49:31.210 --> 00:49:34.645 align:middle line:84%
We will be busy, we will be
manic, we will be hyperactive.

00:49:34.645 --> 00:49:37.090 align:middle line:84%
We'll get a lot of
stuff done every day.

00:49:37.090 --> 00:49:38.990 align:middle line:84%
But our ultimate
goal as a leader

00:49:38.990 --> 00:49:41.710 align:middle line:84%
is to make sure that the team
knows what real success is.

00:49:41.710 --> 00:49:44.010 align:middle line:90%
So that'll be point number two.

00:49:44.010 --> 00:49:46.200 align:middle line:84%
Point three is
all about the idea

00:49:46.200 --> 00:49:50.490 align:middle line:84%
that the principle is this--
if you're alive, you need help.

00:49:50.490 --> 00:49:53.350 align:middle line:84%
So as a leader, you
must be willing not

00:49:53.350 --> 00:49:54.400 align:middle line:90%
to do it all on your own.

00:49:54.400 --> 00:49:57.360 align:middle line:84%
You've got to be willing
to try to allow yourself

00:49:57.360 --> 00:50:00.350 align:middle line:84%
to be receptive and to be
open to support, as well.

00:50:00.350 --> 00:50:01.990 align:middle line:90%
So that's a really big key.

00:50:01.990 --> 00:50:04.170 align:middle line:84%
And the goal, really,
here is the idea

00:50:04.170 --> 00:50:08.570 align:middle line:84%
that, ultimately, none of us
are smarter than all of us.

00:50:08.570 --> 00:50:10.060 align:middle line:90%
So let's get everybody thinking.

00:50:10.060 --> 00:50:12.510 align:middle line:84%
And in particular, in
leadership, the key

00:50:12.510 --> 00:50:14.920 align:middle line:84%
is not to do it
always by yourself.

00:50:14.920 --> 00:50:17.170 align:middle line:84%
There is such a thing as the
loneliness of the leader.

00:50:17.170 --> 00:50:19.820 align:middle line:84%
But often, that loneliness
is self-imposed.

00:50:19.820 --> 00:50:20.910 align:middle line:90%
And it doesn't need to be.

00:50:20.910 --> 00:50:21.743 align:middle line:90%
[END VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:50:21.743 --> 00:50:24.170 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: In that clip, you
talked about leadership.

00:50:24.170 --> 00:50:28.560 align:middle line:84%
And what does that
have to do with love?

00:50:28.560 --> 00:50:29.970 align:middle line:90%
We've talked about happiness.

00:50:29.970 --> 00:50:31.434 align:middle line:90%
We've talked about success.

00:50:31.434 --> 00:50:32.850 align:middle line:84%
Now we've talked
about leadership.

00:50:32.850 --> 00:50:35.040 align:middle line:84%
How does that lead into
the "Loveability" course?

00:50:35.040 --> 00:50:39.510 align:middle line:84%
>>HOLDEN: OK, well, on this
planet, every act of love

00:50:39.510 --> 00:50:42.120 align:middle line:90%
is an act of leadership.

00:50:42.120 --> 00:50:45.140 align:middle line:84%
Fundamentally, the highest
note of leadership--

00:50:45.140 --> 00:50:49.870 align:middle line:84%
when you look at our
planet, deep down, we all

00:50:49.870 --> 00:50:51.790 align:middle line:90%
know we're made of love.

00:50:51.790 --> 00:50:54.710 align:middle line:84%
We all know love
is super important.

00:50:54.710 --> 00:50:57.090 align:middle line:84%
We would all vote
for love in a moment.

00:50:57.090 --> 00:50:59.950 align:middle line:84%
We look around the planet,
and what do we see?

00:50:59.950 --> 00:51:03.690 align:middle line:84%
We're fundamentally seeing
fear, pain, suffering, war.

00:51:03.690 --> 00:51:06.310 align:middle line:84%
And it's like,
something's missing here.

00:51:06.310 --> 00:51:08.280 align:middle line:90%
What's missing?

00:51:08.280 --> 00:51:09.420 align:middle line:90%
Us.

00:51:09.420 --> 00:51:11.260 align:middle line:90%
We're missing.

00:51:11.260 --> 00:51:13.807 align:middle line:84%
How can we get more involved
in the world and in life?

00:51:13.807 --> 00:51:14.890 align:middle line:90%
We've got to show up more.

00:51:14.890 --> 00:51:16.090 align:middle line:90%
How do we show up more?

00:51:16.090 --> 00:51:20.390 align:middle line:84%
We show up as the loving men
and women that we really are.

00:51:20.390 --> 00:51:22.970 align:middle line:84%
When we truly choose
love and we make

00:51:22.970 --> 00:51:26.090 align:middle line:84%
love more important than
anything else, that's you

00:51:26.090 --> 00:51:28.840 align:middle line:84%
and me, Lisa, showing
up as our true selves.

00:51:28.840 --> 00:51:31.210 align:middle line:90%
And that's leadership.

00:51:31.210 --> 00:51:32.420 align:middle line:90%
Who does it affect?

00:51:32.420 --> 00:51:34.570 align:middle line:84%
It affects the person in
front of you right now.

00:51:34.570 --> 00:51:38.230 align:middle line:84%
It affects your family, and
it affects your workplace.

00:51:38.230 --> 00:51:39.800 align:middle line:90%
It affects everybody.

00:51:39.800 --> 00:51:43.140 align:middle line:84%
Love on this planet
is leadership.

00:51:43.140 --> 00:51:46.130 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Take leaders
like Nelson Mandela,

00:51:46.130 --> 00:51:47.960 align:middle line:90%
Mother Teresa, the Dalai Lama.

00:51:47.960 --> 00:51:49.915 align:middle line:84%
Those are leaders
that lead with love.

00:51:49.915 --> 00:51:50.790 align:middle line:90%
>>HOLDEN: Completely.

00:51:50.790 --> 00:51:52.750 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What is the
practical part of it?

00:51:52.750 --> 00:51:55.330 align:middle line:84%
What does the course
teach on this?

00:51:55.330 --> 00:51:58.440 align:middle line:84%
>>HOLDEN: So "Loveability"
is a three-day program

00:51:58.440 --> 00:52:02.280 align:middle line:84%
that I created because I
didn't have a class on love

00:52:02.280 --> 00:52:04.370 align:middle line:90%
when I was at school.

00:52:04.370 --> 00:52:06.210 align:middle line:90%
It just wasn't there.

00:52:06.210 --> 00:52:09.430 align:middle line:84%
The closest we got was
"Romeo and Juliet."

00:52:09.430 --> 00:52:10.480 align:middle line:90%
That was it.

00:52:10.480 --> 00:52:12.760 align:middle line:84%
And it's a good story
with a terrible ending.

00:52:12.760 --> 00:52:15.000 align:middle line:90%
So it's not great.

00:52:15.000 --> 00:52:19.830 align:middle line:84%
When I studied psychology, we
had one lecture on love-- well,

00:52:19.830 --> 00:52:23.685 align:middle line:84%
I don't think it
really was about love.

00:52:23.685 --> 00:52:26.330 align:middle line:84%
The lecture was called
"Interpersonal Attraction

00:52:26.330 --> 00:52:28.250 align:middle line:90%
Theory."

00:52:28.250 --> 00:52:32.260 align:middle line:84%
I remember asking my lecturers,
I said, is this love?

00:52:32.260 --> 00:52:34.885 align:middle line:90%
And they were so noncommittal.

00:52:34.885 --> 00:52:37.440 align:middle line:90%
And I messed with them.

00:52:37.440 --> 00:52:39.422 align:middle line:84%
At Christmas, I sent
them Christmas cards.

00:52:39.422 --> 00:52:41.630 align:middle line:84%
I signed them "with lots of
interpersonal attraction,

00:52:41.630 --> 00:52:43.900 align:middle line:90%
from Robert Holden."

00:52:43.900 --> 00:52:46.600 align:middle line:84%
So in psychology, we didn't
even talk about love.

00:52:46.600 --> 00:52:50.740 align:middle line:84%
And I felt there
was an absence here.

00:52:50.740 --> 00:52:53.300 align:middle line:84%
Even in philosophy,
some of my heroes

00:52:53.300 --> 00:52:54.800 align:middle line:90%
would not talk about love.

00:52:54.800 --> 00:52:55.680 align:middle line:90%
Carl Jung.

00:52:55.680 --> 00:52:58.840 align:middle line:84%
Carl Jung talked about
everything, including UFOs.

00:52:58.840 --> 00:53:00.710 align:middle line:90%
He did not talk about love.

00:53:00.710 --> 00:53:05.110 align:middle line:84%
Krishnamurti, one of my heroes,
would not talk about love.

00:53:05.110 --> 00:53:09.630 align:middle line:84%
Carl Rogers, he talked about
unconditional positive regard.

00:53:09.630 --> 00:53:11.100 align:middle line:90%
But he wouldn't talk about love.

00:53:11.100 --> 00:53:14.050 align:middle line:84%
The reason why so many of these
people wouldn't talk about love

00:53:14.050 --> 00:53:17.570 align:middle line:84%
is because they felt that too
many people had got to the word

00:53:17.570 --> 00:53:21.640 align:middle line:84%
first, and that it
was tainted somehow.

00:53:21.640 --> 00:53:25.210 align:middle line:84%
There was too much
confusion in the word.

00:53:25.210 --> 00:53:27.480 align:middle line:84%
Now, as you know,
Lisa, I believe

00:53:27.480 --> 00:53:28.910 align:middle line:90%
that clarity is the way forward.

00:53:28.910 --> 00:53:31.750 align:middle line:84%
So I feel it's like, let's
not be afraid of these words.

00:53:31.750 --> 00:53:35.090 align:middle line:84%
Let's get back to them and
find some clarity in there.

00:53:35.090 --> 00:53:38.340 align:middle line:84%
So with "Loveability,"
that's my meditation on love.

00:53:38.340 --> 00:53:41.360 align:middle line:84%
That's where I'm saying, let's
get clear about what love is.

00:53:41.360 --> 00:53:44.510 align:middle line:84%
And let's start very,
very clearly with the idea

00:53:44.510 --> 00:53:48.020 align:middle line:90%
that love is not just a word.

00:53:48.020 --> 00:53:51.290 align:middle line:84%
Just in the same way that you
and I are not just bodies,

00:53:51.290 --> 00:53:54.480 align:middle line:84%
it's like we're more than
that, love is not just a word.

00:53:54.480 --> 00:53:56.150 align:middle line:90%
Let's get past the word.

00:53:56.150 --> 00:53:58.640 align:middle line:84%
And when we get past
the word, I think

00:53:58.640 --> 00:54:02.260 align:middle line:84%
what we come to is,
fundamentally, a basic drama.

00:54:02.260 --> 00:54:06.690 align:middle line:84%
The basic drama is that
our unconditioned self

00:54:06.690 --> 00:54:09.050 align:middle line:90%
knows it's loveable.

00:54:09.050 --> 00:54:11.540 align:middle line:84%
And the basic truth of
the unconditioned self

00:54:11.540 --> 00:54:14.720 align:middle line:90%
is I am loveable.

00:54:14.720 --> 00:54:18.990 align:middle line:84%
Now, we have this unconditioned
self, but we move away from it.

00:54:18.990 --> 00:54:22.330 align:middle line:84%
We have that loss of being that
we were talking about earlier.

00:54:22.330 --> 00:54:24.630 align:middle line:84%
And as we move away from
the unconditioned self,

00:54:24.630 --> 00:54:26.660 align:middle line:90%
we create a self-image.

00:54:26.660 --> 00:54:28.390 align:middle line:90%
We create a persona.

00:54:28.390 --> 00:54:31.390 align:middle line:84%
Now, the unconditioned
self believes in love.

00:54:31.390 --> 00:54:32.980 align:middle line:90%
It knows it is loveable.

00:54:32.980 --> 00:54:35.480 align:middle line:84%
The basic truth
is I am loveable.

00:54:35.480 --> 00:54:37.800 align:middle line:90%
The self image has a basic fear.

00:54:37.800 --> 00:54:40.760 align:middle line:84%
The basic fear is
I'm not loveable.

00:54:40.760 --> 00:54:45.460 align:middle line:84%
From that basic fear comes
our myth of inadequacy.

00:54:45.460 --> 00:54:48.600 align:middle line:84%
The myth of inadequacy
is I'm not enough.

00:54:48.600 --> 00:54:51.360 align:middle line:84%
Because I fear I'm not
lovable, I now tell myself

00:54:51.360 --> 00:54:53.450 align:middle line:84%
I'm not beautiful enough,
I'm not smart enough,

00:54:53.450 --> 00:54:56.520 align:middle line:84%
I'm not interesting enough,
I'm not powerful enough.

00:54:56.520 --> 00:54:59.540 align:middle line:84%
That's where the myth of
inadequacy comes from.

00:54:59.540 --> 00:55:02.040 align:middle line:84%
It comes to that fear
that I'm not lovable.

00:55:02.040 --> 00:55:04.020 align:middle line:10%
Now, if we can
tackle that, if we

00:55:04.020 --> 00:55:08.990 align:middle line:10%
can meet that fear face-to-face
and know that it's just a fear,

00:55:08.990 --> 00:55:11.219 align:middle line:10%
that brings us
back to ourselves.

00:55:11.219 --> 00:55:12.760 align:middle line:10%
And in "Loveability,"
what I'm trying

00:55:12.760 --> 00:55:16.440 align:middle line:10%
to do is I'm trying to help
people to see that the way

00:55:16.440 --> 00:55:21.720 align:middle line:10%
to find love is to be the
most loving person you can be.

00:55:21.720 --> 00:55:24.480 align:middle line:84%
The way to love one
person on this planet

00:55:24.480 --> 00:55:28.660 align:middle line:84%
is to be willing to love
everybody on this planet.

00:55:28.660 --> 00:55:33.704 align:middle line:84%
The way to show up fully in
your life is just to-- Rumi

00:55:33.704 --> 00:55:34.370 align:middle line:90%
said it so well.

00:55:34.370 --> 00:55:36.960 align:middle line:84%
He said, "To be a
true human being,

00:55:36.960 --> 00:55:39.610 align:middle line:90%
gamble everything on love."

00:55:39.610 --> 00:55:41.160 align:middle line:90%
Truly.

00:55:41.160 --> 00:55:43.830 align:middle line:84%
Let's just test how
good love really is.

00:55:43.830 --> 00:55:46.550 align:middle line:84%
Let's get past the
word and past the idea

00:55:46.550 --> 00:55:47.940 align:middle line:90%
that it's just a feeling.

00:55:47.940 --> 00:55:50.030 align:middle line:84%
Let's get into
what it really is.

00:55:50.030 --> 00:55:54.030 align:middle line:84%
My daughter, Bo, I was talking
with her about love one day.

00:55:54.030 --> 00:55:56.880 align:middle line:90%
And I asked her what love is.

00:55:56.880 --> 00:55:59.170 align:middle line:84%
Actually, no-- the
actual conversation

00:55:59.170 --> 00:56:03.850 align:middle line:84%
was we were looking at what
we are, what we are made of.

00:56:03.850 --> 00:56:06.320 align:middle line:84%
She was eavesdropping,
actually, on a conversation

00:56:06.320 --> 00:56:07.700 align:middle line:90%
that Holly and I were having.

00:56:07.700 --> 00:56:10.180 align:middle line:84%
I'd been telling Holly that
I was doing this meditation

00:56:10.180 --> 00:56:12.440 align:middle line:90%
on, what are we made of, really?

00:56:12.440 --> 00:56:14.300 align:middle line:90%
What are we made of?

00:56:14.300 --> 00:56:17.210 align:middle line:84%
And Bo, my daughter,
heard this conversation.

00:56:17.210 --> 00:56:18.990 align:middle line:84%
And she just said,
Daddy, it's easy.

00:56:18.990 --> 00:56:20.760 align:middle line:84%
I'll tell you what
we're made of.

00:56:20.760 --> 00:56:22.150 align:middle line:90%
OK, Bo, tell me.

00:56:22.150 --> 00:56:26.010 align:middle line:84%
She said, we're made
of love and water.

00:56:26.010 --> 00:56:27.080 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, how cute.

00:56:27.080 --> 00:56:28.210 align:middle line:90%
>>HOLDEN: Love and water.

00:56:28.210 --> 00:56:28.960 align:middle line:90%
And you know what?

00:56:28.960 --> 00:56:31.140 align:middle line:84%
I just thought,
I'll go with that.

00:56:31.140 --> 00:56:31.900 align:middle line:90%
I'll go with that.

00:56:31.900 --> 00:56:34.800 align:middle line:84%
I think that's what we're
made of, love and water.

00:56:34.800 --> 00:56:36.720 align:middle line:90%
The soul is made of love.

00:56:36.720 --> 00:56:38.630 align:middle line:90%
That's our true nature.

00:56:38.630 --> 00:56:40.640 align:middle line:84%
When we remember
that and when we

00:56:40.640 --> 00:56:43.840 align:middle line:84%
know that love is intelligent--
this is the key bit, Lisa--

00:56:43.840 --> 00:56:45.850 align:middle line:84%
when we know love
is intelligent,

00:56:45.850 --> 00:56:49.020 align:middle line:84%
then we can go to love,
which is our true nature,

00:56:49.020 --> 00:56:52.260 align:middle line:84%
and we can say to love,
show me how to live today.

00:56:52.260 --> 00:56:55.160 align:middle line:84%
Show me how to be the person
I most want to be in the world

00:56:55.160 --> 00:56:55.970 align:middle line:90%
today.

00:56:55.970 --> 00:56:56.950 align:middle line:90%
You guide me.

00:56:56.950 --> 00:56:59.460 align:middle line:84%
You inspire me how
to work in the way I

00:56:59.460 --> 00:57:01.910 align:middle line:84%
want to work, relate in
the way I want to relate,

00:57:01.910 --> 00:57:03.480 align:middle line:90%
and be the person I want to be.

00:57:03.480 --> 00:57:08.260 align:middle line:84%
If we do that, that, I believe,
is what helps us to be happy.

00:57:08.260 --> 00:57:10.650 align:middle line:84%
That's what helps
us to be successful.

00:57:10.650 --> 00:57:12.787 align:middle line:84%
That brings the three
projects together.

00:57:12.787 --> 00:57:13.870 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That is beautiful.

00:57:13.870 --> 00:57:15.620 align:middle line:90%
I love that-- love intelligence.

00:57:15.620 --> 00:57:18.209 align:middle line:84%
It is something that is really
intelligent if you let it be.

00:57:18.209 --> 00:57:19.500 align:middle line:90%
>>HOLDEN: It's completely true.

00:57:19.500 --> 00:57:22.140 align:middle line:84%
When you stop letting love
be a word or a feeling

00:57:22.140 --> 00:57:24.435 align:middle line:84%
and you know it's our
true consciousness,

00:57:24.435 --> 00:57:26.310 align:middle line:84%
that's when we know that
love is intelligent.

00:57:26.310 --> 00:57:28.270 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It's complete knowing.

00:57:28.270 --> 00:57:31.210 align:middle line:84%
Well, thank you so much for
bringing all this together

00:57:31.210 --> 00:57:34.024 align:middle line:84%
to have a conversation about
happiness, success, and love--

00:57:34.024 --> 00:57:34.940 align:middle line:90%
>>HOLDEN: We did well.

00:57:34.940 --> 00:57:35.990 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: --all in
the same context.

00:57:35.990 --> 00:57:36.906 align:middle line:90%
>>HOLDEN: We did well.

00:57:36.906 --> 00:57:37.760 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Absolutely.

